Information
------------------------------

Immigration: Is Britain Really Full?
Is Britain really full? With concerns over the number of people migrating to Britain being one of the key issues of the EU referendum, Tonight reporter Ranvir Singh has travelled around the UK to find out. From London to Lincolnshire, Greater Manchester to Lancashire, Ranvir investigates whether or not our population is really growing too quickly - and asks whether migration brings benefits to our towns and cities, or stretches resources to breaking point.
Britain's population is expected to rise from 65 to 74 million in the next 25 years. In London, that population boom is keenly felt. Partly because of so many migrants coming into the capital, demand for schools, space and housing has rocketed - and property rents there are the second highest in the world.
